snippet: The nonbinding vote by the lower house of Parliament was the latest in a series of moves in Europe that have underlined growing frustration with Israeli policies.
abstract: Lower house of French Parliament votes to recognize Palestinian state in largely symbolic move, in latest show of support for Palestinians and growing wave of European criticism of Israeli policy.

byline.original: By DAN BILEFSKY and MAÏA de la BAUME

lead_paragraph: The nonbinding vote by the lower house of Parliament was the latest in a series of moves in Europe that have underlined growing frustration with Israeli policies.

headline.main: Symbolic Vote in France Backs Palestinian State
headline.print_headline: Symbolic Vote in France Backs Palestinian State
